<article id="query_summary">
  <h2>Given Query versus Executed Query</h2>
  <p>This is presented so you can understand better how my project works.  The
  query on the right is generated by my code, based on the user's query and
  other input, and is the query actually run.  The user-given query is never
  run.</p>
  <div class="left column">
    <h3>Given Query</h3>
    <pre><%= given_query.chomp %></pre>
  </div>
  <div class="right column">
    <h3>Generated Query with Columnar Decomposition</h3>
    <pre><%= generated_query.chomp %></pre>
  </div>
  <br style="clear:both;">
</article>